    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>ACID Properties Demonstration</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n            padding: 0;\n            background-color: #f4f4f4;\n        }\n        h1 {\n            color: #333;\n        }\n        .property {\n            background: #fff;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            margin: 10px 0;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n        #logs {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n            background: #fff;\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            padding: 15px;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n\n<h1>ACID Properties of Databases</h1>\n\n<div class=\"property\">\n    <h2>1. Atomicity</h2>\n    <p>Transactions are all-or-nothing. If part of a transaction fails, the entire transaction fails.</p>\n    <button onclick=\"demonstrateAtomicity()\">Demonstrate Atomicity</button>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"property\">\n    <h2>2. Consistency</h2>\n    <p>Transactions bring the database from one valid state to another, maintaining integrity.</p>\n    <button onclick=\"demonstrateConsistency()\">Demonstrate Consistency</button>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"property\">\n    <h2>3. Isolation</h2>\n    <p>Transactions are isolated from one another until they are committed, preventing interference.</p>\n    <button onclick=\"demonstrateIsolation()\">Demonstrate Isolation</button>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"property\">\n    <h2>4. Durability</h2>\n    <p>Once a transaction is committed, the changes are permanent, even in the case of a system failure.</p>\n    <button onclick=\"demonstrateDurability()\">Demonstrate Durability</button>\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"logs\"></div>\n\n<script>\n    const logs = document.getElementById('logs');\n\n    function logMessage(message) {\n        const logEntry = document.createElement('div');\n        logEntry.textContent = message;\n        logs.appendChild(logEntry);\n    }\n\n    function demonstrateAtomicity() {\n        try {\n            logMessage(\"Starting Transaction...\");\n            logMessage(\"Processing Part 1...\");\n            logMessage(\"Processing Part 2...\");\n            // Simulate an error\n            throw new Error(\"An error occurred!\");\n        } catch (error) {\n            logMessage(\"Transaction Failed: \" + error.message);\n        }\n    }\n\n    function demonstrateConsistency() {\n        logMessage(\"Before Transaction: Balance = $100\");\n        // Simulating a transaction that modifies the balance\n        let balance = 100;\n        balance += 50; // Consistent operation\n        logMessage(\"After Transaction: Balance = $\" + balance);\n    }\n\n    function demonstrateIsolation() {\n        logMessage(\"Transaction 1: Adding $50 to Balance...\");\n        setTimeout(() => {\n            logMessage(\"Transaction 1 Completed: Balance = $150\");\n        }, 1000);\n\n        logMessage(\"Transaction 2: Adding $30 to Balance...\");\n        setTimeout(() => {\n            logMessage(\"Transaction 2 Completed: Balance = $130\");\n        }, 500);\n        \n        logMessage(\"Transactions running in isolation...\");\n    }\n\n    function demonstrateDurability() {\n        let transactionLog = \"Transaction: Added $50\";\n        logMessage(\"Transaction Started...\");\n        logMessage(transactionLog);\n        logMessage(\"Transaction Committed. Changes are permanent.\");\n    }\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
